<br>
<br>
 If your storyline takes place in the present or future then the term &quot; ninja&quot; is extremely out dated. This guy sounds more on the lines of an innocent kid turned single minded professional assassin would be of a more appropriate title for the kid with the serum injection,thanks to involuntary genetic enhancements by the military. From your description he wears something like a cybornetic suit that resembles a ninja costume.<br>
<br>
<br>
 Here's the problem.. why would the military literally capture a teenager? Now terrorist or rebel groups abduct and train children to be come killers but the military unless they are evil and are so vile, that they would go to overboard by kidnapping a teenager.<br>
( I'm assuming it's the US military.. if it were the Middle Eastern or Japan military then its a whole new ball game). Ninjas use shurikens, kunais (small throwing knives). Most people look past all this and just  replace all that with just a cool looking katana sword, although it's truly a samurai's weapon of choice but oh well lol. If the sword fits the character then by all means use it. <br>
<br>
What would be the whole purpose of kidnapping a teenager and making him a mindless killer? In other words, why did the military do this to him?  The thing about a story is that if the teenager can't think or show emotions then all he does is kill and kill, you need to find a way for him to either somewhere down the line reject his orders to kill and maybe he becomes a rogue and then the military starts to send dangerous people after him and either bring him back alive or make sure he dies by sending other ninjas after him who also have been given the serum, maybe those ninjas are teenagers from his neighborhood who also got abducted. <br>
<br>
The other way is to just continue to be a pawn for the military until something out of the ordinary happens, he kills the wrong person and tries to gain back what ever is left of his humanity before the military's influence controls him to continue killing targeted people.<br>
<br>
 The key factors you have to figure out  are the following:<br>
<br>
 -  Who are the bad guys<br>
 - who is the good guy/good guys <br>
 <br>
- what is the objective or goal that the military wants to achieve by tinkering with a serum and using this teenage ninja? More importantly, who do they want him to assassinate and why? <br>
<br>
